  ('emlen-physick-estate', 'Emlen Physick Estate', 'Cape May', '1048 Washington Street', 'NJ', 38.9392, -74.9083, 'mansion', 'Cape May''s original haunted house is an 18-room Victorian mansion designed by renowned architect Frank Furness in 1879. Dr. Emlen Physick lived here with his mother, two maiden aunts, and an array of beloved pets on 14 acres of grounds.', 'Cold spots, disembodied voices, apparitions in period clothing, and phantom footsteps are commonplace. The ghosts include Aunt Emilie, a cheerful socialite who prepared dinner for Dr. Physick''s dogs in the kitchen despite his mother banning them from the house. Aunt Isabella, who died soon after moving in, also lingers. Staff never feel alone and report the spirits of ghost dogs running through the mansion. Cape May MAC has captured dozens of EVP recordings and photographs of ghostly presences here.', 1879, 'https://capemayoceanclubhotel.com/blog/the-emlen-physick-estate-and-the-ghosts-of-cape-may/'),

  ('southern-mansion-cape-may', 'Southern Mansion', 'Cape May', '720 Washington Street', 'NJ', 38.9417, -74.9136, 'mansion', 'Built in 1860, this elegant Italianate mansion served as a seaside summer escape for wealthy businessman George Allen and his family for 83 years. The Atlantic Paranormal Society (TAPS) from Ghost Hunters spent a night here investigating in 2010.', 'The happy ghost of Esther Allen, George Allen''s niece, still lingers in the house enjoying its elegant renovations. Esther reportedly loved parties and social gatherings, and her cheerful presence is felt throughout the beautifully restored rooms. Cold spots, unexplained sounds, and the sense of being watched are commonly reported. Unlike many haunted locations, Esther seems content and welcoming to guests.', 1860, 'https://www.southernmansion.com/blog/cape-may-haunted-mansions/'),

  ('congress-hall-cape-may', 'Congress Hall', 'Cape May', '251 Beach Avenue', 'NJ', 38.9319, -74.9061, 'hotel', 'Built by Congressman Thomas Hughes in 1816 and originally called "Tommy''s Folly" due to its massive size, Congress Hall was destroyed in Cape May''s Great Fire of 1878 but quickly rebuilt. The landmark hotel has hosted U.S. Presidents including Ulysses S. Grant.', 'Victims of the devastating 1878 fire that destroyed the original Congress Hall may still haunt the current building. Spirits attached to the original structure linger in the halls and guest rooms. Guests report unexplained footsteps, cold spots, and the sensation of ghostly presences in their rooms. The elegant Victorian atmosphere seems to attract spirits who wish to relive Cape May''s golden age.', 1816, 'https://www.southernmansion.com/blog/ghostly-encounters-cape-may-haunted-tours-and-spooky-tales/'),

  ('inn-at-cape-may', 'The Inn at Cape May', 'Cape May', '7 Ocean Street', 'NJ', 38.9297, -74.9067, 'hotel', 'The 1894 Victorian-style, five-story inn commands a large property at the corner of Beach Street and Ocean Street. Walking into the lobby is like stepping back in time with glorious Victorian decor, chandeliers, and a huge fireplace.', 'The most active spirits are those of a young boy and girl, with the girl identifying herself as "Annie." The child ghosts are most active in rooms 88 and 92, but they knock on doors of other guest rooms at night. Since the year it opened, a double drowning has left three ghostly residents wandering the halls. Guests report mysterious footsteps, doors opening and closing, and the laughter of children in empty corridors.', 1894, 'https://hauntedhouses.com/new-jersey/the-inn-at-cape-may/'),

  ('angel-of-the-sea', 'Angel of the Sea B&B', 'Cape May', '5 Trenton Avenue', 'NJ', 38.9306, -74.9050, 'hotel', 'This stunning Victorian B&B features gingerbread trim, towering turrets, and a wraparound porch that gives it a storybook appearance. The beautifully restored building is one of Cape May''s most photographed properties.', 'Staff report at least four ghosts, including a young woman whose mother was a caretaker and father a sea captain - she can be seen looking out to sea waiting for his return. Another spirit died of tuberculosis within these walls. A third ghost plays tricks on staff, moving objects and creating mischief. The peaceful Victorian atmosphere belies the supernatural activity that occurs regularly throughout the building.', 1850, 'https://www.hauntedrooms.com/new-jersey/haunted-places/haunted-hotels/angel-of-the-sea'),

  ('hotel-macomber', 'Hotel Macomber', 'Cape May', '727 Beach Avenue', 'NJ', 38.9317, -74.9111, 'hotel', 'One of Cape May''s most notoriously haunted locations, this boutique hotel has operated since 1911. The intimate property offers guests the choice to stay in the room with the most paranormal activity.', 'Multiple spirits haunt the Macomber, including a waitress in shabby clothing who haunts the dining room and kitchen. Room 11 experiences the most activity - inexplicable banging on the door late at night, disembodied voices, and clothes being stolen from guests. One terrified guest was pushed into the walk-in refrigerator by an unseen force. The hotel embraces its haunted reputation and guests can request the most active rooms.', 1911, 'https://www.hauntedrooms.com/new-jersey/haunted-places/haunted-hotels'),

  ('cape-may-lighthouse', 'Cape May Lighthouse', 'Cape May Point', 'Cape May Point State Park', 'NJ', 38.9317, -74.9597, 'lighthouse', 'The 1859 Cape May Lighthouse features 199 steps up an original cast iron spiral stairway offering views of the Delaware Bay and Atlantic Ocean. The lighthouse has guided mariners past this treacherous point for over 160 years.', 'Those who lost loved ones to the sea were left haunted, sorrowfully lingering at the lighthouse. The spirits of drowned sailors and shipwreck victims are said to wander the grounds. Cape May''s location at the convergence of the Delaware Bay and Atlantic Ocean has claimed countless ships over the centuries. Ghost tours describe the lighthouse as a creepy place to visit after dark, where brazen pirates, lonely maids, and Cape May''s watery phantoms still dwell.', 1859, 'https://capemaymac.org/ghosts-mysteries/'),

  ('chalfonte-hotel', 'The Chalfonte Hotel', 'Cape May', '301 Howard Street', 'NJ', 38.9378, -74.9092, 'hotel', 'The oldest operating hotel in Cape May, the Chalfonte has been welcoming guests since 1876. The sprawling Victorian structure maintains its historic character with minimal modern updates, creating an authentic 19th-century atmosphere.', 'The hotel is haunted by Mr. Johnson, a former custodian who has been spotted in the basement going about his duties as if still employed. The apparition of a woman holding a baby has been seen at the top of the hotel in the cupola, gazing out at the sea. Mr. Johnson is described as a dedicated worker who seems unaware that his employment ended long ago, continuing to maintain the building he loved in death as he did in life.', 1876, 'https://usghostadventures.com/uncategorized/top-ten-most-haunted-places-in-cape-may/');

