  ('burlington-county-prison', 'Burlington County Prison Museum', 'Mount Holly', '128 High Street', 'NJ', 40.0058, -74.7875, 'prison', 'Designed by architect Robert Mills (who also designed the Washington Monument), this 1811 prison was the oldest continuously-used prison in the U.S. when it closed in 1965. Featured on Ghost Hunters, it''s considered one of New Jersey''s most haunted sites.', 'Joel Clough, imprisoned for stabbing his girlfriend to death, was held in the dungeon after an escape attempt and hanged in 1833. Guards and inmates reported moaning, rattling chains, and cigarette smoke from his empty cell. His body is buried in the prison yard under a large tree. A child''s spirit hides in the old safe. Full-bodied shadows move across rooms. The dungeon - where prisoners were chained to the floor before execution - often leaves visitors breathless.', 1811, 'https://weirdnj.com/stories/garden-state-ghosts/burlington-prison/'),

  ('smithville-mansion', 'Smithville Mansion', 'Eastampton', '803 Smithville Road', 'NJ', 40.0153, -74.7894, 'mansion', 'This Greek Revival mansion built in 1840 sits on a 250-acre compound once known as Shreveville. Hezekiah B. Smith, an inventor, politician, and bigamist, bought the property in 1865 with his "second" wife Agnes, more than 20 years his junior.', 'Paranormal groups have documented ghost activity including piano music playing when no one is at the piano, lights flickering, and apparitions of people walking through walls. Hezekiah and Agnes are believed to still lurk around. After Agnes died in 1881, Hezekiah arranged to be buried in an iron coffin sunk in concrete near her. His son ordered Agnes'' statue destroyed and thrown in the river. The creepy dolls, human hair portrait, and moose head add to the mansion''s ghoulish atmosphere.', 1840, 'https://www.cbsnews.com/philadelphia/news/smithville-mansion-burlington-county-halloween-weddings/');

