  ('absecon-lighthouse', 'Absecon Lighthouse', 'Atlantic City', '31 South Rhode Island Avenue', 'NJ', 39.3672, -74.4153, 'lighthouse', 'At 171 feet, Absecon Lighthouse is the tallest lighthouse in New Jersey and third tallest in the United States. Built in 1857 and decommissioned in 1933, it has been featured on Syfy''s Ghost Hunters due to its extensive paranormal activity.', 'Many lost souls haunt the lighthouse - reports of spirits have been common since 1905. A pipe-smoking sailor is often seen staring out to sea from the top. Ghostly figures wander around the base of the tower. Footsteps are heard on the spiral staircase with no one there. The main entrance opens and closes on its own. The lighthouse attracted sailors for generations, and some seem unable to leave even after death.', 1857, 'https://usghostadventures.com/atlantic-city-ghost-tour/the-history-and-ghosts-of-absecon-lighthouse/'),

  ('flanders-hotel', 'The Flanders Hotel', 'Ocean City', '719 East 11th Street', 'NJ', 39.2806, -74.5625, 'hotel', 'Built on the Ocean City boardwalk in 1923, this landmark hotel''s hauntings are the most talked about in the Atlantic City area. The massive hotel has underground catacombs that add to its mysterious atmosphere.', 'Emily, the Lady in White, is a pretty, cheerful apparition with long brown hair who wanders the hallways in bare feet. She appears and disappears into walls, plays with door locks, and unscrews light bulbs. The catacombs are haunted by a little girl who drowned and died while being carried through the tunnels. Ghosts of mob victims eliminated during illicit activities in the hotel''s heyday as a gangster hangout are tortured souls in the underground passages.', 1923, 'https://weirdnj.com/stories/garden-state-ghosts/emily-haunts-the-flanders-hotel-ocean-city/'),

  ('resorts-casino-hotel', 'Resorts Casino Hotel', 'Atlantic City', '1133 Boardwalk', 'NJ', 39.3750, -74.4197, 'hotel', 'Atlantic City''s first casino hotel was used as "Camp Boardwalk" during WWII, serving as a base of operations and wartime hospital. The Ocean Tower is particularly active with supernatural phenomena.', 'WWII soldiers who died when the building was a hospital are seen throughout the halls, still preparing for war. A mysterious apparition of a man flipping his top hat - possibly Charlie Chaplin''s ghost - appears to guests. Cold spots and unexplained elevator noises are common. One terrifying incident involved a guest''s door shaking violently in the middle of the night by an unseen hand. The trauma of wartime echoes into the present.', 1978, 'https://phillyghosts.com/top-10-haunted-places-in-atlantic-city/'),

  ('jonathan-pitney-house', 'Jonathan Pitney House', 'Absecon', '57 North Shore Road', 'NJ', 39.4219, -74.4964, 'mansion', 'The beautifully restored 1800s home of Jonathan Pitney, known as the "Father of Atlantic City." Pitney was instrumental in developing the railroad that transformed the area into a resort destination.', 'Pitney reportedly told his wife Caroline that she had to live in their home forever - and she seems to have taken him literally. Visitors feel a presence in her room and hear bells ringing throughout the house when no one is there. Caroline''s spirit is described as gentle but persistent, watching over the home her husband built and the legacy he created.', 1799, 'https://nyghosts.com/top-ten-most-haunted-atlantic-city/'),

  ('estell-manor', 'Estell Manor', 'Estell Manor', 'Route 50', 'NJ', 39.4108, -74.7497, 'other', 'Located in the vast Pine Barrens, this Atlantic County park contains abandoned buildings, ruins, and multiple cemeteries from the 19th century. The manor was once a thriving community before industry declined and residents departed.', 'Ghostly orbs and shadow people are frequently seen around the abandoned structures. The Abbott house is haunted by the spirit of a little girl who plays and bounces a ball - believed to be the ghost of the Abbotts'' adopted daughter who arrived after they lost two sons in infancy. The combination of Pine Barrens isolation, abandoned buildings, and forgotten cemeteries creates an intensely haunted atmosphere throughout the park.', 1800, 'https://usghostadventures.com/atlantic-city-ghost-tour/top-10-most-haunted-places-in-atlantic-city/');

