  ('trenton-psychiatric-hospital', 'Trenton Psychiatric Hospital', 'Trenton', 'Sullivan Way', 'NJ', 40.2281, -74.7314, 'hospital', 'Founded in 1848 by mental health advocate Dorothea Dix, this was the first public institution to use the Kirkbride Plan. Under Dr. Henry Cotton (1907-1933), the hospital became a house of horrors where barbaric surgical experiments were performed without anesthesia.', 'Dr. Cotton believed infections caused mental illness, so he removed teeth, gallbladders, stomachs, colons, and reproductive organs from living patients. Many died. His apparition is seen wandering the halls in his doctor''s jacket. Ghosts of patients with missing limbs appear throughout the facility. Screams and moans echo from patient rooms. The suffering of thousands has left an indelible mark. The facility still operates with 400 beds, though many wards are abandoned.', 1848, 'https://the-line-up.com/trenton-psychiatric-hospital'),

  ('kendall-hall-trenton-state', 'Kendall Hall at TCNJ', 'Ewing', '2000 Pennington Road', 'NJ', 40.2678, -74.7833, 'university', 'A historic building on The College of New Jersey campus (formerly Trenton State College), Kendall Hall has been home to theatrical performances and academic programs for over a century.', 'The ghost of Sigrid Stevenson haunts Kendall Hall, making her presence known during theatrical performances. Strange noises are heard in Holman Hall as well. Students and staff report unexplained sounds, cold spots, and the feeling of being watched during late-night rehearsals. The theatrical tradition seems to attract spirits who wish to experience the performances.', 1929, 'https://weirdnj.com/stories/ghosts-index/');

