VALUES
  ('barnegat-lighthouse', 'Barnegat Lighthouse ("Old Barney")', 'Barnegat Light', 'Barnegat Lighthouse State Park', 'NJ', 39.7644, -74.1067, 'lighthouse', 'Locally nicknamed "Old Barney," this historic lighthouse at the northern tip of Long Beach Island has guided mariners since 1859. The 172-foot tower replaced an earlier lighthouse that fell into the sea as the shoreline eroded.', 'The waters around Barnegat Inlet are the site of the 1782 Massacre at Barnegat, where Captain John Bacon ordered the throats of 21 sailors slit ear to ear. Tortured moaning and wailing come from the dunes, and blurry images of men in old sailor outfits appear on foggy nights. Shipwreck victims from centuries of maritime disasters also haunt the lighthouse grounds, drawn to the beacon that failed to save them.', 1859, 'https://usghostadventures.com/long-beach-island-ghost-tour/'),

  ('surf-city-hotel', 'Surf City Hotel', 'Surf City', '8th Street and Long Beach Boulevard', 'NJ', 39.6619, -74.1692, 'hotel', 'One of Long Beach Island''s oldest landmarks, famous for lavish pre-Prohibition parties. The hotel overlooked the site of the tragic Powhatan shipwreck that claimed over 200 lives in 1854.', 'The ghosts of the Powhatan shipwreck haunt the hotel. Over 200 men, women, and children traveling from Europe to New York perished when the ship encountered a devastating storm off the New Jersey coast. Guests see a transparent woman holding a baby looking out windows. Screams of dead passengers are heard. Spirits wander the halls aimlessly, still confused about their fate. Apparitions in period clothing appear throughout the building.', 1870, 'https://phillyghosts.com/top-10-haunted-places-in-atlantic-city/'),

  ('dios-cafe', 'Dios Cafe', 'Beach Haven', '401 North Bay Avenue', 'NJ', 39.5592, -74.2261, 'restaurant', 'A charming cafe on Long Beach Island known for its food and one very unusual regular customer from the other side. The building has been a gathering place for locals and visitors for generations.', 'The cafe is haunted by the ghost of a deep-sea diver who perished over a hundred years ago. He still wears his decaying diving gear, including a corroded diving helmet. The diver appears to customers and staff, a tragic figure from LBI''s maritime past. His presence serves as a reminder of the dangers faced by those who worked the waters around Long Beach Island.', 1900, 'https://usghostadventures.com/long-beach-island-ghost-tour/');

