  ('centenary-university', 'Centenary University', 'Hackettstown', '400 Jefferson Street', 'NJ', 40.8536, -74.8292, 'university', 'Named by Reader''s Digest as one of the 10 most haunted colleges in America. In 1886, when the school was Centenary Collegiate Institute, 18-year-old kitchen maid Tillie Smith was murdered in a field behind the school.', 'Tillie had asked janitor James Titus to let her back in after curfew. Instead, he attempted to rape her and strangled her to death. He served 17 years in prison. Tillie''s ghost walks among the oak trees, floats on ceilings in South Hall, and frequents the theater backstage. A girl in white has been seen walking along roads and even gets into cars before disappearing. Legend says she appears in a sorority photo taken after her murder, kept under lock and key.', 1867, 'https://weirdnj.com/stories/garden-state-ghosts/tillie-smith-centenary-college/'),

  ('greystone-park-psychiatric', 'Greystone Park Psychiatric Hospital', 'Morris Plains', '59 Koch Avenue', 'NJ', 40.8406, -74.4817, 'hospital', 'Founded in 1876, Greystone had the largest building foundation in the United States until the Pentagon was built. At its peak, over 7,700 patients lived in overcrowded conditions. Folk singer Woody Guthrie was a patient here, calling it "Gravestone."', 'Shadowy figures, disembodied voices, and sudden temperature drops are common. The ghost of a nurse still tends to long-departed patients. A young girl in a pink dress appears in corridors. Greenish lights with no identifiable source float through wards. The underground tunnels used to transport patients are extremely creepy. Though the main Kirkbride building was demolished in 2015, the spirits seem unable to leave. The 2012 horror film "Greystone Park" was inspired by the location.', 1876, 'https://weirdnj.com/stories/greystone-park-psychiatric-hospital/'),

  ('inn-of-the-hawke', 'Inn of the Hawke', 'Lambertville', '74 South Union Street', 'NJ', 40.3633, -74.9428, 'hotel', 'A popular inn and restaurant built in the 1860s in charming Lambertville along the Delaware River. The building has served travelers between New Jersey and Pennsylvania for over 150 years.', 'Several different ghosts haunt the property, including one notorious spirit named "Cinnamon." Strange occurrences and noises are regularly reported. In the kitchen, pots and pans have been lifted off their hooks before crashing onto the floor. Staff have grown accustomed to the supernatural activity, though new employees are often startled by their ghostly coworkers.', 1860, 'https://www.newjerseyhauntedhouses.com/real-haunt/inn-hawke.html'),

  ('union-cemetery-hackettstown', 'Union Cemetery', 'Hackettstown', 'Route 46', 'NJ', 40.8500, -74.8278, 'cemetery', 'The final resting place of Tillie Smith, the murdered kitchen maid of Centenary University. Her marble monument was paid for by locals who contributed money to provide her with a proper burial.', 'Tillie''s gravestone bears a simple, powerful epitaph: "She died in defense of her honor." Her ghost has been seen not only at the campus but here at her grave. Visitors report cold spots, the feeling of being watched, and occasionally catching glimpses of a young woman in 19th-century clothing standing near her monument. Tillie seems to visit both the place of her death and her eternal rest.', 1800, 'https://www.newjerseyhauntedhouses.com/real-haunt/union-cemetery.html');
